<TITLE> <b>International children's film fest from Saturday</b> </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Jan 22 (bdnews24.com)  The second international children's film festival will be held in Dhaka on Jan. 24-30 with the slogan 'the future dream in frames'. As many as 156 films of 4o countries including Bangladesh will be screening in the weeklong festival, film director Morshedul Islam, one of the organisers of the festival committee, told a press conference at the National Press Club on Thursday. The inaugural ceremony will be held at Central Public Library Auditorium at around 4pm. The venues are British Council, German Cultural Centre, Russian Cultural Centre, Iranian Cultural Centre and Alliance Franchise. The special show of 'Little Piece of Mine', a documentary made on the brutality on children by Israel, will be screened on Jan. 29 at Public Library Auditorium. A five-member jury board of the festival will select five best films. Bangladesh is participating in the festival with 35 movies, of which 15 are made by children. Children Film Society is organising the festival. b
